Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Tripsacum dactyloides KS

Assembly is haploid, and the genome is paleotetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 2600 Mb, and has 18 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Tripsacum dactyloides KS from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Dotplot of Tripsacum dactyloides KS vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Tripsacum dactyloides KS along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Tripsacum dactyloides KS is a paleotetraploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 2 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Tripsacum dactyloides KS

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Tripsacum dactyloides KS along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Tripsacum dactyloides KS is a paleotetraploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 2 lines for each subgenome.
